Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

I'm split on this one as I agree that not altering migrations is important, however, I see that this improves the process being done. I'd like to get a better consensus on if we think it is okay to change these files or not from a broader audience. If everyone agrees. I will change to +1. Otherwise, I like the goal of this change.

Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

So one of the reasons why these kind of changes are not allowed in the migration scripts is that anyone who has triggers notifying change on the migration script would need to dig in and figure out why that script was changed and then understand if the change on the script their deployment has ran already needs an action.

I'm fully with Mike here, as this is not critical nor security related change, the existing migration scripts should not be changed.

While Rob's reasoning is valid, I'd also like to point out it was request for people to stop converting the iteritems() via massive regexps, not a request to dump next massive regexp to change it again ;)
